              ]
            },
            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 1.0,
                  "response": "Thatâ€™s correct!"
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: With groupthink, suggesting alternative ideas is perceived as disloyal. LO 5.5 Be familiar with the effects of group size on stability, intimacy, attitudes, and behavior; types and styles of leaders; the Asch experiment on peer pressure; the Milgram experiment on authority; and the implications of groupthink."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Instead of shifting away form the problem at hand, groupthink involves a narrowing of thought. LO 5.5 Be familiar with the effects of group size on stability, intimacy, attitudes, and behavior; types and styles of leaders; the Asch experiment on peer pressure; the Milgram experiment on authority; and the implications of groupthink."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Groupthink is more closely linked to not thinking about things carefully enough. LO 5.5 Be familiar with the effects of group size on stability, intimacy, attitudes, and behavior; types and styles of leaders; the Asch experiment on peer pressure; the Milgram experiment on authority; and the implications of groupthink."
                }
              }
